1.00	Blue_Grama	Bouteloua gracilis	Blue Grama, Bouteloua gracilis, is a long-lived, warm season, C4 perennial grass native to North America. It is most commonly found from Alberta east to Manitoba and south across the Rocky Mountains, Great Plains, and Midwest states to Mexico. Blue grama accounts for most of the net primary productivity in the shortgrass prairie of the central and southern Great Plains.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/85/Bouteloua_gracilis.jpg/220px-Bouteloua_gracilis.jpg
